description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for Fixed Term Clinical Fellow (ST1/2 level) posts in Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology at Southmead Hospital for 2 months commencing December 2nd 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Obstetric Unit at Southmead Hospital is one of the major Units in the country, there being 6,400 deliveries per annum dealing with a full range of both normal and abnormal Obstetrics. The Gynaecology ward has over 4,000 admissions per annum and there are 11 major gynaecology operating lists per week. The post is very suitable for interested career obstetricians and gynaecologists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Registration with the GMC is essential.The post is based at Southmead Hospital. The Trust has teaching status and is linked with the University of Bristol and the University of the West of England. Experience and familiarity with UK hospital systems and practices or equivalent is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is not recognised for training and does not have postgraduate deanery approval. However, the job is educationally sound. Candidates must have, or be eligible for, GMC registration that allows them to work in posts that are not recognised for training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The annual basic salary is in accordance with the ST 1/2 Scale is as follows £38,694. Additional supplements will be added if participation on the out of hours rota is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are shortlisted we will contact you by email with details of your interview of which you will need to confirm your attendance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries may be made to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr Susie Hogg, Consultant&lt;/strong&gt; via email: susannah.hogg@nbt.nhs.uk or via telephone 0117 414 6751&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or &lt;strong&gt;Dr Naomi Jobson, Consultant &lt;/strong&gt;via email: naomi.jobson@nbt.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note North Bristol NHS Trust will not pay interview expenses in connection with this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: Thursday 12th Nov (midnight)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: Monday 16th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Late applications will not be accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Committed to equal opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
